OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FJailed Iran activist       
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdescribes brutality in     
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fletter                     
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, One of Iran's most prominent female    
OL,6, activists has described how confessions
OL,7, are forced out of prisoners, in a      
OL,8, letter written inside a notorious jail.
OL,10,FSepideh Qolian has been serving a      
OL,11,Ffive-year sentence since 2018 after    
OL,12,Fbeing convicted of acting "against     
OL,13,Fnational security" for supporting a    
OL,14,Fstrike.                                
OL,16,FWriting from Evin prison, she describes
OL,17,Fthe brutal treatment of her and other  
OL,18,Fdetainees by interrogators.            
OL,20,FTheir forced confessions are later     
OL,21,Fbroadcast on state-run television.     
